rComments: The exam was nothing like the midterms! She added stuff on the exam that wasn't on her exam review, completely unfair, would not recommend this prof

Omg, she has to be one of the nicest profs ever! 2 midterms and 1 final. She makes study guides for all 3 exams. And if you study exactly what is mentioned in the study guide, you are guaranteed A+. The only question she asks outside of the guide is bonus question. (The only way you could do poorly is if you are terrible at memorizing).
Really great prof, cares about her students, exams are super fair. Really great class overall!

You can tell she cares about her student and wants them to succeed. But has difficulty answering questions, usually has to get back to you . She knows her slides, but not much beyond whats on there. For the final she completely changed her format and added things we hadnt covered in class.
She is probably the nicest Prof I have had in all of undergrad. Really wants her students to succeed and is very approachable. Highly recommend!

10/10 Great prof - knows what she's talking about, answers questions well in class - really nice. Gives review outlines for midterms and finals (no one else has ever made me one) and midterms and finals are very clearly laid out - relate to the content - if you study, you'll do really well. No "trick questions" or "pick the MOST correct" M/C.
